# Phase 16: Fixing XAML Runtime Crash (DownloadPage)

This phase addresses the "flash-back" crash reported by the user. The investigation revealed that [DownloadPage.xaml](file:///C:/Users/Linyizhi/.gemini/GeminiLauncher/Views/DownloadPage.xaml) is missing several critical resource declarations and a namespace definition, leading to a `XamlParseException` at runtime.

## Proposed Changes

### 1. XAML Repairs
#### [MODIFY] [DownloadPage.xaml](file:///C:/Users/Linyizhi/.gemini/GeminiLauncher/Views/DownloadPage.xaml)
- Add `xmlns:conv="clr-namespace:GeminiLauncher.Converters"` to the [Page](file:///C:/Users/Linyizhi/.gemini/GeminiLauncher/Views/HomePage.xaml.cs#9-17) tag.
- Add `<Page.Resources>` section.
- Declare the following resources:
    - [BooleanToVisibilityConverter](file:///C:/Users/Linyizhi/.gemini/GeminiLauncher/Converters/InverseBooleanToVisibilityConverter.cs#8-20) (Standard)
    - `conv:StringMatchToBoolConverter`
    - `conv:ProgressToIconConverter`
- Ensure the `iOS26.Background` is correctly applied to the main `Grid`.

## Verification Plan

### Automated Tests
- `dotnet build` to ensure all XAML references are resolved.

### Manual Verification
- Launch the application.
- Click "Download" in the sidebar.
- Verify the page loads without crashing and displays the version list.
